text: Moonshine is an unincorporated community and census-designated place in St. James Parish, Louisiana, United States. Its population was 194 as of the 2010 census. The community is located on the west bank of the Mississippi River. ==Geography== According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the community has an area of ; of its area is land, and is water. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in St. James Parish, Louisiana Category:Unincorporated communities in Louisiana Category:Census-designated places in St. James Parish, Louisiana Category:Census-designated places in Louisiana
